	errors are found that reach up to 40 nm for typical system parameters
	and aberration levels at the diffraction limit. These are systematic
	errors that are independent of the total photon count in the image.
	The gaussian function is therefore inappropriate, and more sophisticated
	PSF models are a practical necessity.},
